comments: Vanessa is a great teacher. I love her and wish she wasn\'t gone! Very intimidating at first but worth the effort getting used to her. She\'s gone now due to having a baby.

Shes an awesome instructor.. a bit intimidating but its only because she wants you to really know what you are giving a patient and why. Shes very caring and helpful.. So sad she wont be back to teach anymore

Vanessa is really nice but a little intimidating at first until you get to know her. Gives a lot of feedback for care plans/ concept map. Leaves you alone during clinical but expects you to be very thorough when answering med questions while giving meds. Passed everyone in my clinical (thats saying a lot). Very good, highly recommend.
she has the tendency to choose favorites. she thinks she\'s superior at times and is intimidating, but she\'s not at all! sometimes shes not respectful

Had her for NURS1A and NURS1B. She is awesome! The epitome of a compassionate nurse and educator. She may have high standards but she will support you so you can meet those standards. If you want to learn, definitely take her!
This teacher has both good bedside and theory knowledge. Smart, helpful, and hot!
